Three suspected gangsters on Tuesday night escaped after police raided their hideout in Karen, Nairobi.Area OCPD Cunningham Suiyanka said three pistols and 51 bullets were recovered.He said when officers approached the hideout, the gangsters fired at them as they escaped on foot.The suspects are said to have dropped their weapons.Police acted on a tip off by members of the public that the three were planning to rob area residents.Suiyanka asked residents to remain vigilant and report any suspicious activities in the area as police pursue the suspects.